---
const symptoms = [
  'Redness and flakes between the eyebrows, in the creases beside your nose, sometimes the hairline or beard edge',
  'It comes back in the same spots every time, no matter what you switch',
  'It calms down after a new product or an exfoliation, then returns days later',
];
---

<section class="panel" id="problem">
  <div class="container problem">
    <div class="problem__intro">
      <span class="eyebrow">Sound familiar?</span>
      <h2>Same spots. Every time.</h2>
      <p class="verdict">
        That was me for years. If it's you too, this is almost certainly
        <strong>seborrheic dermatitis</strong>. Extremely common, not a hygiene
        problem, and not something you can scrub away. Very controllable once
        you know what's actually happening.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="symptoms">
      {symptoms.map((s) => (
        <li>
          <svg class="symptoms__check" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true" width="22" height="22">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="11" fill="var(--color-accent)" />
            <path d="M7 12.5 L10.5 16 L17 8.5" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-ink)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          </svg>
          <span>{s}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .verdict { font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: 0; }

  .symptoms {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }
  .symptoms li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .symptoms__check {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.2em;
  }

  @media (min-width: 860px) {
    .problem {
      grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
